2.5.3 Internal Algorithms & Operational Logic
* Hybrid Semantic & Exact Retrieval (BM25 + Vector Search with RRF): When executing QueryMemory, implements a hybrid dual-retrieval pipeline:
   1. Vector Similarity Search: Embeds query_text into $Q_{\text{vec}}$ (768-dim) and executes an approximate nearest neighbor search against FactualFacts using Spanner's ScaNN vector index (APPROX_COSINE_DISTANCE), retrieving top $K=30$ semantic candidates.
   2. Exact Lexical BM25 Search: Concurrently executes a full-text token matching query across title and factual_content using Spanner token search indexes, retrieving top $K=30$ lexical candidates.
   3. Reciprocal Rank Fusion (RRF): Combines and reranks results from both candidate sets: $$\text{RRF_Score}(n) = \sum_{m \in {\text{vec}, \text{lex}}} \frac{1}{60 + \text{rank}_m(n)}$$
* Fact Deduping & Superseding Consensus Engine: During WriteMemory, checks existing active facts in the store for cosine similarity $\ge 0.92$ (distance $\le 0.08$). If a near-duplicate exists, updates the existing fact by appending source_provenance_uris and incrementing confidence_score. If contradictory operational directives are detected via NLI text classification, invokes ProposeConsensusFact to gate modifications behind human sign-off.


