4. Key Schema Architectural Mechanism Explanations
4.1 Recursive Sub-Task Trees (parent_task_id & Interleaving)
To model arbitrary engineering decomposition (Epic $\rightarrow$ Feature $\rightarrow$ Task $\rightarrow$ Actuation Step), the Tasks table defines a self-referential foreign key constraint:


CONSTRAINT FK_Tasks_Parent FOREIGN KEY (workstream_id, parent_task_id) REFERENCES Tasks (workstream_id, task_id)

* Data Locality: Because Tasks is interleaved in Workstreams, all sub-tasks belonging to a workspace are physically co-located on the same Spanner database server split.
* Single-Hop Traversals: Querying an entire sub-task hierarchy executes in a single local network hop using GoogleSQL recursive Common Table Expressions (CTEs), avoiding cross-partition distributed locking and guaranteeing sub-10ms tree assembly.
4.2 Multi-Source Provenance Arrays (original_sources & source_provenance_uris)
Tasks and memories frequently converge from disparate channels (e.g., a bug thread buganizer://b/123, a discussion gmail://space/xyz, and a CL cl/456).


* Array Normalization: Storing these as native Spanner arrays (ARRAY<STRING(1024)>) eliminates secondary junction tables (TaskSources or MemoryCitations), keeping schema footprint compact.
* Auditability & Deduplication: When duplicate detection merges a new trigger into an existing canonical task, Spanner array append functions record the new source URI. This preserves an unbroken, auditable chain of custody explaining why a task was created or why an agent rule was synthesized.
4.3 Semantic Vector Embeddings (vector_embedding with ScaNN Indexing)
Both Tasks and FactualFacts maintain 768-dimensional dense float arrays indexed via Spanner's native ScaNN (Scalable Nearest Neighbors) index type with cosine distance metrics.


* In-Database ANN: Executing vector similarity search directly within Spanner (APPROX_COSINE_DISTANCE) eliminates external vector database ETL pipelines and synchronization lag.
* Millisecond Triage: During task ingestion or memory recall, ScaNN evaluates thousands of candidate centroids in sub-10ms latency, powering semantic deduplication and cluster consolidation natively at scale.
4.4 Fine-Grained Agent Permission Toggles (MemoryACLs)
Memory security is strictly governed by interleaved ACL records under MemoryStores.


* Dual Identity Binding: grantee_identity binds to both human Gaia IDs and agent service accounts (workstream-agent-sobi@system.gserviceaccount.com).
* HITL Hard Gating: The require_hitl_for_write boolean acts as an immutable database gate. When an agent attempts to call WriteMemory on a TEAM or GLOBAL store, MemoryService evaluates this flag. If true, the commit is intercepted and held in abeyance; a notification card is pushed to FeedService requiring explicit human sign-off before the record is written to Spanner.


